Males constitute 55% of the population and females 45%. Quammruddin Nagar has an average literacy rate of 67%, higher than the national average of 59.5%: male literacy is 73%, and female literacy is 58%. In Quammruddin Nagar, 17% of the population is under 6 years of age. ==References== {{Reflist}} [[Category:Cities and towns in West Delhi district]] {{Delhi-geo-stub}}
